waffleoRai_cafebotCommands

Class BotScheduler.PermanentPositionMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • waffleoRai_cafebotCommands.BotScheduler.PermanentPositionMap
  • Enclosing class:
    BotScheduler

    public static class BotScheduler.PermanentPositionMap
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class for a String to Integer HashMap used for mapping command strings to constant bot indices.
    This map is used to associate commands with bots that will always handle that given command, regardless of the current shift.
    Since:
    July 1, 2018
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Blythe Hospelhorn

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public int get(java.lang.String key)
        Get the index of the bot set to handle the given command string.
        Parameters:
        key - String representation of command to retrieve associate bot for.
        Returns:
        Index of bot set to handle command key, or -1 if command is not recognized or no bot is set.

      • put

        public void put(java.lang.String key,
                int botIndex)
        Add a command string/bot index mapping. Once a bot index is mapped to a command string, the Scheduler will always return that bot index for that command, regardless of the current shift setting.
        Parameters:
        key - Command string to map bot to.
        botIndex - Index of bot to set.

        Get the set of all command strings (map keys) currently in this map.

        A copy of the internal map's keyset as a HashSet.
